500 g Chorizo Sausage, uncased
170 g Rigatoni
56 g Baby Spinach
1 unit(s) Cream Cheese
7 g Parsley
½ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
¼ cup Roasted Pepper Pesto
1 tsp Chili Flakes
56 g Yellow Onion, chopped
1 tsp Garlic Salt
1 cup Marinara Sauce
0.13 tsp Pepper*
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
0.13 tsp Salt*

Roughly chop spinach.
Roughly chop parsley.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When the pan is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, then onions, turkey and 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) chili flakes. (NOTE: Reference heat guide.)
Cook, breaking up turkey into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Season with garlic salt.

Meanwhile, add rigatoni to the boiling water. Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender, 8-10 min.
Reserve 1/2 cup (1 cup) pasta water, then drain.

Add cream cheese, marinara, roasted pepper pesto, 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar and 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) reserved pasta water to the pan with turkey mixture.
Cook, stirring often, until cream cheese melts and sauce comes to a simmer.
Reduce heat to medium. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until sauce thickens slightly, 2-3 min.

Add rigatoni and half the Parmesan to the pan. Stir until cheese melts and sauce coats rigatoni. (NOTE: Add remaining reserved pasta water, 2 tbsp at a time, to loosen the sauce, if desired.)
Add spinach and stir until wilted, 1 min. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rigatoni between plates. Sprinkle with parsley, remaining Parmesan and any remaining chili flakes, if desired.

If you've opted for double chorizo, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the regular portion of chorizo. Work in batches, if necessary.